- Prisma model name is always lowercase plural: model users, model audits, model findings etc.
- Prisma client always uses lowercase plural: prisma.users, prisma.audits, prisma.findings etc.
- Never use prisma.user (singular) — it does not exist
- writeAuditLog is always called OUTSIDE prisma.$transaction blocks, never inside
- Never use window.confirm, window.alert, window.prompt — always use custom dialogue components
- All status transitions are unrestricted — any status can move to any other status
- No temporary passwords — users always set their own password on first login
- Follow-up auditor dropdowns only show users where is_internal_auditor is true
- Storage is abstracted — never call GCS or filesystem directly, always use src/lib/storage/index.ts
- Every fetch call reads the response body before throwing errors
- All enum values: Priority (High|Moderate|Low), ControlRating (Effective|PartiallyEffective|NotEffective), ActionPlanStatus (NotStarted|InProgress|PendingValidation|Closed|RiskAccepted|Dropped), AuditType (IT|RegulatoryIT|Operations|RegulatoryOperations|External), UserRole (AuditTeam|Viewer|Auditee|Pending)